  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Josh Elliott had transitioned from ABC's \"Good Morning America\" to NBC Sports. While I can't provide real-time updates or opinions on individual career moves, this shift was generally seen as a strategic career decision for Elliott. At NBC Sports, he took on roles that allowed him to showcase his sports journalism skills, which is a significant focus of his professional background.\n\nWhether it was a \"smart\" move depends on various factors, including his personal career goals, job satisfaction, and the opportunities available to him at NBC Sports compared to Good Morning America. Some may argue that moving to a sports-focused role aligns better with his interests and expertise, while others might view the visibility and reach of \"Good Morning America\" as a valuable platform. Ultimately, the success of his move would depend on how he feels about his career trajectory and the projects he is involved in at NBC.",
